Shield
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:esp. the Ranfurly Shield (an interprovincial rugby union trophy); occas. the Plunket Shield q.v. (a former interprovincial cricket trophy). also attrib. or comb: esp. SHIELD GAME, SHIELD MATCH) (cf. LOG-OF-WOOD) see also PLUNKET SHIELD, RANFURLY SHIELD [The Ranfurly Shield was presented by His Excellency the Earl of Ranfurly, Governor [?General] of New Zealand and patron of the NZ Rugby Football Union September 13 1902]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
